This Pep Boys business has been cited for not enough screening on its dumpster enclosure area. This fence is to add more screening to resolve the issue with the City of Irving. The east side of dumpster enclosure on the side on shipping container will have a 25’ section of steel pipe fence built 8’ high. Steel post bases will be used and anchored into concrete curb (solid blue line on aerial photo). Steel will be painted and 8’x6” privacy cedar fence pickets will be fastened to the steel. The north end of the dumpster enclosure will have a 50’ section on fence built with three 12’ wide double gates (blue and red alternating lines on aerial photo. Red lines represent approximate gate locations. Gate locations will be confirmed with MOD). These gates will be manual only and no electricity will be run to them.Gate posts will be 6”x1/4” pipe buried 3’ in the ground and set in concrete. Current concrete slab will need to be cored out to allow for these gate posts to be installed. Heavy duty weld on hinges will be used to secure gates.Fence sections of this north fence will be 8’ privacy fence with cedar pickets. Gates will be custom made of steel, painted, and have 8’ cedar privacy fence pickets secured to them. 6 gates total will need to be made and measure 6’ wide X 8’ high to allow for 12’ gate openings to access the shipping container, dumpster, and recycling container. Gates will have cane bolts to allow locking in open and closed position.Utilities survey will be located prior to performing any work.
